"'''Bungo n' Rusti Get Carry-Out'''" is a short comic story written by [[James Anderson|Jim Anderson]] published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 11|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 11]] by [[West End Games]] in November 1996.

==Plot summary==
[[Bungo Bung]] and his droid co-[[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[42-RST|Rusti]] arrive on [[Sullust/Legends|Sullust]]. Bung is hungry, so he visits the local [[Biscuit Baron]] for a meal of [[Bantha Breakfast Biscuit]]s with [[blue sauce]]. While eating, Bung mentions that thousands of people in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] have never tasted a Bantha Breakfast Biscuit. Rusti replies that he should fill up the hold with them and find a market to sell them in. After a small debate regarding [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub]] company policy, he relents and fills the ''[[Chubby Gundark]]''{{'s}} hold.

After liftoff, the ''Chubby Gundark'' is intercepted by a [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] commanded by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Wankle]]. All but one crate of the cargo is confiscated. Regardless of this setback, Bung travels to the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] world of [[Gastrula]] and establishes the [[Great Bantha Breakfast Biscuit Run]]. Two weeks later, Bung discovers that the biscuits are mutating into [[Giant Amorphous Bantha Breakfast Biscuit]]s. Bung and Rusti narrowly avoid the destruction of their ship by defeating the creature with blue sauce. With one case left, they allow it to be confiscated by Captain Wankle as revenge for his original confiscation of their cargo&mdash;but slyly regret that they have no blue sauce to go with it.

==Legacy==
Subsequent ''[[Bungo n' Rusti]]'' stories were originally slated to appear in later issues of the ''Adventure Journal'', but, as [[Dark Horse Comics]] held the sole ''[[Star Wars]]'' comics license, the plans were scrapped. Several more unofficial stories were published online at [[TheForce.net]], but only the first comic is considered official.

